subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. This species is unique in having the uncus with middle emargination extremely shallow; the gnathos with middle process short, not reaching anterior margin of tegumen, not hook-shaped but sub-triangular or only with an extremely short hook; the sacculus rather long and narrow, about 1/4 length of valva ( Figs 6 ,
35– 35g
). It can be further distinguished from its allies by the triangular subgenital plate in the female genitalia ( Figs 40–43 ). In addition, this species with phallus bearing more microthorns (mostly more than thirty) than other species on average.
